# Source documentation
This source files provide the solver and test cases used in "Laminar flow-induced scission kinetics of polymers in dilute solutions" by Etienne Rognin, Niamh Willis-Fox, Tommy Z. Zhao, Talal A. Aljohani, and Ronan Daly.

## Disclaimer
This source code is released in the hope that it will be useful, but without any warranty.

## License
This source code follows OpenFOAM licensing. You can redistribute it and/or modify it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or (at your option) any later version. See  [http://www.gnu.org/licenses/](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/)

## Content
* pimpleMechanoChemFoam: source for the solver
* capillary: case folder for the fused glass capillary flow.
* pinhole25: case folder for the pinhole 25 flow.
* pinhole50: case folder for the pinhole 50 flow.


## Installation and usage
* Install OpenFOAM v6. Source code [here](https://github.com/OpenFOAM/OpenFOAM-6).

* Install the solver using the standard OpenFOAM procedure for new solvers (see OpenFOAM documentation).

* Run the case using the pimpleMechanoChemFoam command, or, for parallel runs the provided bash scripts.

